  <Method>
    <Step image="">In a large bowl (earthenware crock, if you have one), place the artichokes, hearts of palm, olives, capers, cheese, salami and roasted peppers. Add the bay leaves and black pepper.</Step>
    <Step image="">In a blender, add olive oil, balsamic vinegar and anchovies. Puree for a minute.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add portions of the reserved liquids of the canned/jarred ingredients to your taste, until you have enough liquid to almost cover the contents of the bowl, you can add more olive oil and balsamic vinegar as you wish and blend the ingredients.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add salt to taste.</Step>
    <Step image="">Pour the contents of the blender into the bowl. </Step>
    <Step image="">Add parsley, stir to mix. Cover an chill for at least a day before serving to allow the flavors to marry. </Step>
  </Method>
